usage: git wip [<options>] <wip-suffix> -- <module-paths>
   or: git wip [<options>] --finish     -- <module-paths>

Start or finish WIP mode.

    -h|--help               display help
    -r|--recursive)         visit modules recursively
                            true if --finish option is specified and current module is a bundle
    --finish                finish WIP mode
    <wip-suffix>            WIP suffix
    <module-paths>          list of specific modules to visit
    
example:
    git wip 'work'              # start WIP mode "work' in current module and bundle
    git wip 'work' -- sm1 sm2   # start WIP mode "work' in modules sm1 and sm2 and bundle
    git wip --finish            # finish WIP mode of current module or all
                                # submodules if current module is a bundle 
